<h2>How to Measure SEO ROI and Adjust Your Budget</h2>
<p>The median SEO ROI in 2026 reaches 748%, with organizations seeing $22 in returns for every $1 invested, according to <a href="https://firstpagesage.com/reports/seo-roi-statistics-fc/">First Page Sage's ROI report</a>. But that number means nothing if you are not tracking your own ROI.</p>
<h3>The ROI Formula</h3>
<p><strong>SEO ROI = (Revenue from organic traffic - SEO investment) / SEO investment x 100</strong></p>
<p>To calculate this, you need:
- Total organic traffic (from GA4)
- Conversion rate for organic visitors
- Average customer value
- Total SEO spend (all 5 categories combined)</p>
<p>Use the <a href="/tools/seo-roi-calculator/">SEO ROI calculator</a> to run this quickly.</p>
